Make sure to create a `.env` file in the root directory to hold your environment variables.

MONGO_URI=<your_mongo_connection_string>

Replace `<your_mongo_connection_string>` with your actual MongoDB URI connection string, which you can obtain from MongoDB Atlas or your local MongoDB setup.

### Summary of file structure:
/project-root
  /models
    Entry.js
  /routes
    /api
      entries.js
  db.js
  server.js
  .env

This setup will allow you to submit data through the HTML form and store it in a MongoDB database using Express.js and Mongoose. Make sure to install the required packages (`express`, `mongoose`, `dotenv`). You can do this via:

npm install express mongoose dotenv